by Marc O. Gloor. It will display the current system load, used memory
and cpu time based on the output of the linux process filesystem which
must be mounted before. This release doesn't support command line options,
all features are hardcoded. Xmon is self self explaining, therefore no
manpage is available. Further development has been terminated.
d28 3
d35 1
a35 3
<p>I published the code in the hope that someone would spend some time
to expand the source. However, the code is published under the terms of
the GNU GPL.
